<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HEAT VENTILATION AIR CONDITIONING (HVAC), Orifice Tube System, Pre-March 2007 - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300,
        4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700, 8500, 8600 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - A/C REFRIGERANT LINE (DISCHARGE LINE
        COMPRESSOR-TO-CONDENSER)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>A/C REFRIGERANT LINE (DISCHARGE LINE COMPRESSOR-TO-CONDENSER)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1602523">Figure 24</hotlnk>
                        while performing the following Remove and Install procedures.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discharge the A/C system. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16025_HL1602528.xml" xrefid="hl1602528">DISCHARGING THE SYSTEM</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl1602528"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Depending on the model, it may be necessary to remove nearby assemblies (right splash
                    panel, fixed grille, or recirculation shield) to gain access to the fittings, or to remove the A/C
                    lines. Refer to HOOD, GRILLE, and FENDERS section in GROUP 09- FRONT END SHEET METAL in the Master
                    Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If applicable, unclip hose support clamps (3), and/or tie-wraps, securing
                    compressor-to-condenser line.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1602523" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602523A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                             scalefitheight="472px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 24. A/C Refrigerant Line (Compressor-to-Condenser) (Shown with Recirculation Shield
                        and Splash Panel Removed)
                    </caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. COMPRESSOR</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. COMPRESSOR-TO-CONDENSER LINE</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. HOSE SUPPORT CLAMPS</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. CONDENSER</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect line (2) fitting from condenser (4).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect compressor-to-condenser line (2) fitting at compressor (1).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove compressor-to-condenser line (discharge line).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the system is to be flushed or purged, perform that operation before reassembling the
                    system. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16025_HL1602525.xml" xrefid="hl1602525">PURGING OR FLUSHING THE AIR CONDITIONING
                        SYSTEM
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl1602525"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place compressor-to-condenser line (2) in approximate location.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Always lubricate O-rings with mineral-based oil during installation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a new O-ring and C-plate connect compressor-to-condenser line fitting at
                    compressor (1). Tighten to 20,000 &#177;1000 N.mm (180 &#177;10 lbf-in).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a new O-ring and C-plate connect compressor-to-condenser line fitting at condenser
                    (4) inlet. Tighten to 20,000 &#177;1000 N.mm (180 &#177;10 lbf-in).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the line using support clamps (3) and/or tie-wraps, as applicable.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install any assemblies that were removed to gain access to the compressor-to-condenser
                    line (such as right splash panel, fixed grille, or recirculation shield). Refer to HOOD, GRILLE, and
                    FENDERS section in GROUP 09- FRONT END SHEET METAL in the Master Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Recharge the system. Refer to:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <hotlnk document="s16025_HL1602526.xml" xrefid="hl1602526">OIL FILL GUIDELINES</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="hl1602526"/>;
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <hotlnk document="s16025_HL1602529.xml" xrefid="hl1602529">EVACUATING THE SYSTEM</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="hl1602529"/>;
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <hotlnk document="s16025_HL1602530.xml" xrefid="hl1602530">CHARGING THE AIR CONDITIONING
                            SYSTEM
                        </hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="hl1602530"/>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
